{
  "question_text": "<h3>Spiral Matrix</h3><p>Given an `m x n` matrix, return all elements of the matrix in spiral order.</p>",
  "difficulty": "MEDIUM",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "Space-separated values as per problem arguments.",
  "output_format": "A single line representing the result.",
  "constraints": [
    "1 <= N <= 10^5"
  ],
  "explanation": "We use four boundaries (top, bottom, left, right) and shrink them inward as we traverse the matrix in a clock-wise direction. Time complexity O(M*N).",
  "answer": "class Solution:\n    def solve(self, matrix: List[List[int]]) -> List[int]:\n        res = []\n        left, right = 0, len(matrix[0])\n        top, bottom = 0, len(matrix)\n        while left < right and top < bottom:\n            for i in range(left, right):\n                res.append(matrix[top][i])\n            top += 1\n            for i in range(top, bottom):\n                res.append(matrix[i][right - 1])\n            right -= 1\n            if not (left < right and top < bottom): break\n            for i in range(right - 1, left - 1, -1):\n                res.append(matrix[bottom - 1][i])\n            bottom -= 1\n            for i in range(bottom - 1, top - 1, -1):\n                res.append(matrix[i][left])\n            left += 1\n        return res",
